Working at Argent Energy is an opportunity to develop, to grow and a place to optimally develop your career. We offer a varied working environment where you can grow both personally and professionally. Argent Energy is a waste-based biodiesel producer with three operational locations in Scotland, England and the Netherlands.
With the production of biofuel, Argent Energy wants to make a direct contribution to the global fight against climate change! Argent Energy has been part of the Swire Group since November 2018. John Swire & Sons Ltd. stems from a family business founded in 1816, which has grown in 200 years into a global company with various participations in aviation, maritime, food, trading and industry.
We set ourselves the goal of expanding our production in our plant in Amsterdam. To achieve this, we want to expand our project team with a:

Project Engineer (civil) | full time

Location: Amsterdam
As Project Engineer at Argent Energy will be responsible for the site infrastructure designs including, site layouts, road layouts, site logistics, drainage designs, cut and fill assessments, electrical ducting infrastructure and drawings to relevant standards.

You will be an active player in all stages of our project from basic design to construction completion and have the opportunity to work with multi-disciplinary sub-contractors. You will be working as a part of a project team, but we expect you to be able to work independently and be responsible for your own work both quality and accuracy point of view.

Your responsibility will be to checking and monitoring engineering offices, sub-contractors, field technicians and field installation works.

The Department

The Project Team is responsible for the realisation of the complete project. The working language in this department is English.
Requirements

You recognize yourself in the following competencies: highly organised with attention to details, ambitious, quality-conscious, multi-tasking, resilient attitude, 'out of the box' thinker and a teamplayer. You also bring:

A completed bachelor or master degree in civil engeering, construction or similar with at least 5 years of industrial work experience;
Experience with AutoCad, Cadmatic and AutoCad Plant 3D;
Oil & Gas industry and/or Energy Plants and/or Chemical Plants experience is an advantage;
Experience in working with building companies;
Experience of using excel and Auto Cad to advanced level;
Experience of checking and verifying calculations for concrete foundation, steel structures;
Additional Experience of verifying mechanical process equipment calculations;
Familiar with the relevant NEN and EN norms;
Excellent written and oral communication skills.

What do we Offer?

Good primary and secondary employment conditions and an attractive pension scheme;
A bonus scheme based on stated business results (max 10% of yearly salary);
Working to an sustainable future with 120 passioned colleagues and lots of room for personal development.
What's next?

Interested? Send us your resume and motivation letter in English today!

To respect the GDPR regulations, we cannot process your personal data without permission. That is why we strongly recommend that you apply directly through our work-at site. Applications by e-mail will not be taken into consideration in this context.

Acquisition as a result of this vacancy is not appreciated.
Any questions?
Then contact Richard Witte (HR Manager). Richard can be reached by phone at 020-2192930.

Are you a Process Engineer with affinity with the listed tasks and do you meet the requirements below? Then we would like to stay in touch with you for future opportunities!
You can apply to this vacancy and we will contact you when new opportunities arise.

Duties:
Developing, configuring and optimizing industrial processes from inception through to start up and certification;

Preparing process flow schemes (PFD's) and determining process control systems;

Calculating and developing mass and heat balances;

Calculates and specifies process equipment and prepares process specifications for control valves, pressure-relief valves, flow- and temperature meters and pressure measuring instruments;

Preparing process safeguarding diagrams;

Determining maximum and minimum process and safety conditions;

Developing process and instrumentation diagrams (P&ID's) together with piping and mechanical engineers;

Calculating pipe diameters and pressure drops in pipes and piping systems for one-phase and multiple-phase flows;

Creating process descriptions and operating manuals;

Controlling quality of produced documents.

Job requirements:
3 to 15 years relevant experience or equivalent;

Bachelor or Master in Process or Chemical Engineering;

Excellent knowledge of the Dutch or English language;

Residence within The Netherlands. Applicants that do not live within The Netherlands will not be taken into consideration;

Full permission to work in the EU. Applicants that do not have this permission will not be taken into consideration.
